[h3 id=Overview 
	" Overview
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Aims to expand the site's library of unique and interesting TASes.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Showcases both unique speed goals and entertainment-based playarounds.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" 
		(__wikiLink|displaytext=Applicable Movie Rules|href=/MovieRules#Alternative)
		".
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=TechnicalRequirements 
	" Technical requirements
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Must beat all known records, including other TASes.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Must show a proficient understanding of TAS techniques and be perceived as well optimized: It should not have obvious pauses, mistakes, or sloppy play.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=GoalChoice 
	" Goal choice
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Goals should make sense within the context of the game, and should be explainable to a general audience.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Goals should offer a different experience from other runs, particularly 
		(__wikiLink|href=/Standard|implicitdisplaytext=standard)
		" runs.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" Goals shouldn't just be random, nonspecific actions for the sake of trying to "guarantee" a publication.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[h3 id=Entertainment 
	" Entertainment
	$LF
]h3
[ul 
	[li 
		" Any run that aims for entertainment over speed, such as playarounds, are curated by entertainment.
		$LF
	]li
	[li 
		" This will be assessed via votes, comments, and views from the general community.
	]li
]ul
